The '''chestnut-shouldered goshawk'''<!--, '''Autour De Bürger''', or '''Azor De Bürgers'''--> ('''''Erythrotriorchis buergersi''''') is a species of [[bird of prey]] in the family [[Accipitridae]]. It is found in [[New Guinea]]. It has a length of 43 to 53 cm and a wingspan of 85 to 109 cm.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Ferguson-Lees |first=James |title=Raptors of the World |date=2005 |publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing Plc |others=David A. Christie |isbn=978-0-7136-6957-2 |series=Helm Field Guides |location=London}}</ref>

